– 2 –
1 (II) The costs of supervising each nurse apprentice who
2 participates in the program and is employed by the health care
3 entity; and
4 (III) Retention bonuses paid by the health care entity to
5 each nurse apprentice who participates in the program and enters
6 into an employment agreement with the health care entity upon
7 graduation and licensure;
8 (2) Travel expenses incurred by a nurse apprentice who
9 participates in the program and resides more than 50 miles from his
10 or her employing health care entity; and
11 (3) Administrative costs to carry out the program, except not
12 more than $500,000 of the money appropriated by subsection 1 may
13 be used for this purpose.
14 3. Any remaining balance of the appropriation made by
15 subsection 1 must not be committed for expenditure after June 30,
16 2027, by the entity to which the appropriation is made or any entity
17 to which money from the appropriation is granted or otherwise
18 transferred in any manner, and any portion of the appropriated
19 money remaining must not be spent for any purpose after
20 September 17, 2027, by either the entity to which the money was
21 appropriated or the entity to which the money was subsequently
22 granted or transferred, and must be reverted to the State General
23 Fund on or before September 17, 2027.
24 4. As used in this section:
25 (a) “Health care entity” means:
26 (1) A medical facility;
27 (2) A community health clinic; or
28 (3) A health maintenance organization.
29 (b) “Nurse apprentice” means a nursing student who performs
30 tasks that he or she has successfully demonstrated in his or her
31 program of education in accordance with regulations adopted by the
32 State Board of Nursing.
33 (c) “Nursing student” means a person who is:
34 (1) Enrolled in a program of professional nursing or practical
35 nursing at an accredited school of nursing;
36 (2) Taking at least three credits of nursing theory or clinical
37 courses related to nursing in an academic semester; and
38 (3) Continuously progressing toward obtaining a certificate
39 or degree in nursing.
40 Sec. 2. This act becomes effective upon passage and approval.
